## Redirect to: [Scottish Lowlands](/Scottish_Lowlands)

This particular entry serves as a direct conduit, guiding you to the comprehensive article detailing the [Scottish Lowlands](/Scottish_Lowlands). For those unfamiliar, the [Scottish Lowlands](/Scottish_Lowlands) represent one of the three major geographical and historical divisions of [Scotland](/Scotland), situated generally south and east of the [Highland Boundary Fault](/Highland_Boundary_Fault). While geographically less mountainous than their northern counterparts, they encompass a rich tapestry of history, culture, and significant urban development, including the nation's capital, [Edinburgh](/Edinburgh), and its largest city, [Glasgow](/Glasgow). This redirect ensures that various search terms or common references can efficiently lead users to the primary, authoritative source of information on this crucial region, circumventing potential confusion or search frustrations for those who might employ a slightly different nomenclature.

