This particular redirect serves to guide users to the designated article title in strict accordance with established [naming conventions](/Wikipedia:Naming_conventions), specifically those pertaining to the use of [common names](/Wikipedia:Common_names). The philosophy behind favoring [common names](/Wikipedia:Common_names) is rooted in accessibility and user expectation; it aims to title articles using the name that is most widely recognizable and naturally understood by the general English-speaking public. This approach significantly aids both searches and the process of writing new content, as it reduces ambiguity and promotes intuitive navigation.

